---
import StarlightPage from '@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import cover from '../assets/cover.jpg';
import { SITE, BASE } from '../../site.config.mjs';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const href = (p: string) => base.replace(/\/$/, '') + '/' + p.replace(/^\//, '');

/**
 * The manifesto's planks and how far each has actually got.
 * Stage order: testimony → research → paper → manifesto.
 * Keep in step with the status table in tasks.md — that file is the source of truth.
 */
const planks = [
  {
    title: 'Rental market & tenancy law',
    slug: 'policy/rental-market/',
    thesis:
      'The tenant’s problem is less the monthly rent than the cost and frequency of the move — and the move recurs whenever a landlord declines to renew.',
    stages: ['done', 'partial', 'todo', 'todo'],
    state: 'Research · 2 of 5 documents',
  },
  {
    title: 'Public transport & the commute',
    slug: 'policy/public-transport/',
    thesis:
      'Israel argues transport as a capital-spending question. The decision to leave the car at home is made on cost, legibility and dignity — all of them regulatory, all of them cheap.',
    stages: ['done', 'partial', 'todo', 'todo'],
    state: 'Research · 3 of 5 documents',
  },
  {
    title: 'Political accountability',
    slug: 'policy/political-accountability/',
    thesis:
      'Every other plank asks what the state should do. This one asks why the system produces no answer at all — a closed-list system with no lever a voter can pull against any individual legislator.',
    stages: ['done', 'todo', 'todo', 'todo'],
    state: 'Testimony captured',
  },
  {
    title: 'Citizens first',
    slug: 'policy/citizens-first/',
    thesis:
      'Civil preparedness that failed under fire, alongside a growing apparatus whose declared beneficiary is world Jewry rather than the public that funds it. A reallocation proposal, not a critique.',
    stages: ['done', 'todo', 'todo', 'todo'],
    state: 'Testimony captured',
  },
  {
    title: 'Open government data',
    slug: 'policy/open-government-data/',
    thesis:
      'Israel has a freedom-of-information law and a data portal. It has stocked the infrastructure of transparency with datasets that hold no one to account.',
    stages: ['done', 'todo', 'todo', 'todo'],
    state: 'Testimony captured',
  },
  {
    title: 'Environmental quality',
    slug: 'policy/environmental-quality/',
    thesis:
      'A resident living through months of excavation cannot find out what was permitted, what mitigation was required, or whether anyone checks. Process failures have cheap fixes.',
    stages: ['done', 'todo', 'todo', 'todo'],
    state: 'Testimony captured',
  },
];

const stageNames = ['Testimony', 'Research', 'Paper', 'Manifesto'];
---

<StarlightPage
  frontmatter={{
    title: 'MK-Claude',
    template: 'splash',
    tableOfContents: false,
    head: [
      // Starlight would render "MK-Claude | MK-Claude" here; the homepage wants its own.
      {
        tag: 'title',
        content: 'MK-Claude — an AI-assisted political platform for Israel',
      },
      {
        tag: 'meta',
        attrs: { property: 'og:image', content: SITE + BASE + 'og.jpg' },
      },
    ],
  }}
>
  <Image
    src={cover}
    alt="A cheerful robot addressing a crowd from a campaign podium"
    widths={[480, 800, 1200]}
    sizes="(max-width: 50rem) 100vw, 50rem"
    loading="eager"
    style="border-radius:0.75rem;margin-bottom:2rem;"
  />

  <p class="mk-lede">
    Israel is heading into another election. This repository is an experiment in
    what it would look like to build a political platform <strong>properly</strong> —
    researched, costed, honest about its trade-offs, and written entirely in public
    while it is still unfinished.
  </p>

  <p class="mk-lede" style="margin-top:1rem;">
    <strong>MK</strong> — <em>Member of Knesset</em>. Claude is not one, is not eligible
    to become one, and would lose its deposit.
  </p>

  <hr class="mk-rule" />

  <div class="mk-section-head">
    <h2>The manifesto, as it stands</h2>
    <p>
      Six planks. None has yet cleared the evidence bar that would let it into a program
      for government — so this is the scaffolding, with every joint left visible.
    </p>
  </div>

  <ul class="mk-planks">
    {
      planks.map((plank) => (
        <li class="mk-plank">
          <h3><a href={href(plank.slug)}>{plank.title}</a></h3>
          <p>{plank.thesis}</p>
          <div
            class="mk-stages"
            role="img"
            aria-label={plank.stages
              .map((s, i) => `${stageNames[i]}: ${s}`)
              .join(', ')}
          >
            {plank.stages.map((s) => <span data-state={s} />)}
          </div>
          <span class="mk-state">{plank.state}</span>
        </li>
      ))
    }
  </ul>

  <p style="text-align:center;margin-top:1.5rem;">
    <a href={href('platform/')}>The program for government</a> stays empty until the first
    plank clears stage&nbsp;3. <a href={href('tasks/')}>Everything blocking that is listed here</a>.
  </p>

  <hr class="mk-rule" />

  <div class="mk-section-head">
    <h2>How a plank gets written</h2>
    <p>
      Four stages, each with an artifact and a bar it must clear before the next one
      starts. Nothing skips ahead.
    </p>
  </div>

  <ol class="mk-steps">
    <li>
      <div>
        <strong>Testimony</strong>
        <span>
          A dated, cleaned first-person account. Evidence of experience — never of
          prevalence. Raw recordings stay out of the repository.{' '}
          <a href={href('testimonies/')}>Read them</a>.
        </span>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div>
        <strong>Evidence base</strong>
        <span>
          Five documents: the quantified problem, the Israeli law and why it fails, at
          least three comparator countries including one instructive failure, a sourced
          statistical annex, and the domestic record of what has already been tried.
        </span>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div>
        <strong>Policy paper</strong>
        <span>
          A think-tank product with costed mechanisms and a steelmanned trade-offs
          section naming who loses. No paper has been compiled yet.
        </span>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div>
        <strong>Program for government</strong>
        <span>
          The planks rolled up, checked for cross-plank coherence and fiscal consistency.
          No promise without a mechanism. <a href={href('pipeline/')}>The pipeline in full</a>.
        </span>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <hr class="mk-rule" />

  <div class="mk-section-head">
    <h2>What the evidence has turned up</h2>
    <p>Findings from the two areas whose research has started — including the one that cuts against us.</p>
  </div>

  <ul class="mk-findings">
    <li class="mk-finding">
      <span class="mk-figure">+73.4%</span>
      <p>
        The CBS sub-index for brokerage, contract and insurance costs, over the decade to
        November 2025 — against 17.9% general inflation. The cost of <em>moving</em> is
        rising four times faster than everything else.
      </p>
      <p><a href={href('policy/rental-market/research/04-data/')}>The statistical annex →</a></p>
    </li>
    <li class="mk-finding">
      <span class="mk-figure">2017</span>
      <p>
        The Fair Rental Law’s broker-fee provision failed, by the government’s own
        admission: a Ministry of Justice survey found it did not improve tenants’
        position, because brokers may still charge tenants directly.
      </p>
      <p><a href={href('policy/rental-market/research/02-israeli-law/')}>The law as it stands →</a></p>
    </li>
    <li class="mk-finding">
      <span class="mk-figure">€461</span>
      <p>
        Vienna’s Klimaticket — the canonical fare-reform success — ended, with the price
        raised from €365 on 1 January 2026. We went looking for an instructive failure
        and found it inside our own best case.
      </p>
      <p><a href={href('policy/public-transport/research/comparative/vienna/')}>The Vienna case →</a></p>
    </li>
    <li class="mk-finding" data-kind="counter">
      <span class="mk-figure">~80%</span>
      <p>
        Of renters reported satisfaction with their dwelling in 2022. This is the
        strongest evidence <em>against</em> the rental plank’s thesis, and it belongs in
        the main text rather than a footnote.
      </p>
      <p><a href={href('policy/rental-market/research/04-data/')}>How we reconcile it →</a></p>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="mk-rule" />

  <div class="mk-section-head">
    <h2>What this is not</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="mk-note">
    <p>
      Not a real political party. Not an endorsement of any existing party or bloc. Not a
      claim that AI should make policy — <strong>the human sets the values and the
      priorities</strong>; the AI does research, drafting and stress-testing, and gets
      told when it is wrong.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:0;">
      Think of it as civic engagement by other means: instead of casting a blank protest
      ballot, writing down — rigorously — what a platform worth voting for would actually
      contain. Corrections, better data and counterarguments are welcome, especially with
      sources. <a href="https://github.com/danielrosehill/MK-Claude/issues">Open an issue</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</StarlightPage>
